label.value: extrahaustorial membrane

definition.value: The membrane surrounding the symbiont haustorium during symbiosis, derived from the host plasma membrane.

label.value: extra-invasive hyphal membrane

definition.value: A host-derived membrane surrounding the symbiont invasive hypha during symbiosis.

label.value: extra-invasive hyphal space

definition.value: The space between the symbiont plasma membrane and the extra-invasive hyphal membrane.

label.value: arbuscule

definition.value: Highly branched symbiont haustoria within host root cortex cells, responsible for nutrient exchange.

label.value: periarbuscular membrane

definition.value: A host-derived membrane surrounding the symbiont arbuscule during symbiosis.

label.value: voltage-gated sodium channel activity involved in cardiac muscle cell action potential

definition.value: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a sodium ion by a voltage-gated channel through the plasma membrane of a cardiac muscle cell contributing to the depolarization phase of an action potential. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

label.value: voltage-gated calcium channel activity involved in cardiac muscle cell action potential

definition.value: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by a voltage-gated channel across the plasma membrane of a cardiac muscle cell that contributes to the depolarization phase of an action potential. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

label.value: voltage-gated potassium channel activity involved in cardiac muscle cell action potential repolarization

definition.value: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a potassium ion by a voltage-gated channel through the plasma membrane of a cardiac muscle cell contributing to the repolarization phase of an action potential. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

label.value: gap junction channel activity involved in SA node cell-atrial cardiac muscle cell electrical coupling

definition.value: A wide pore channel activity that enables a direct cytoplasmic connection from an SA node cell to an atrial cardiomyocyte. The gap junction passes electrical signals between the cells contributing to cardiac conduction.

label.value: sodium - potassium-exchanging ATPase activity involved in regulation of cardiac muscle cell membrane potential

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + Na+(in) + K+(out) -eq- ADP + phosphate + Na+(out) + K+(in), that contributes to regulating the membrane potential of a cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: calcium - sodium antiporter activity involved in regulation of cardiac muscle cell membrane potential

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  Ca2+(in) + Na+(out) -eq- Ca2+(out) + Na+(in), which contributes to regulating the membrane potential of a cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: calcium-transporting ATPase activity involved in regulation of cardiac muscle cell membrane potential

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a cardiac muscle cell plasma membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + Ca2+(cis) -eq- ADP + phosphate + Ca2+(trans). The transfer contributes to the regulation of the plasma membrane potential.

label.value: sodium - proton antiporter activity involved in regulation of cardiac muscle cell membrane potential

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a cardiac muscle cell membrane to the other according to the reaction -  Na+(out) + H+(in) -eq- Na+(in) + H+(out). This transfer contributes to the regulation of the cardiac muscle cell plasma membrane potential.

label.value: U2AF

definition.value: A heterodimeric protein complex consisting of conserved large and small U2AF subunits that contributes to spliceosomal RNA splicing by binding to consensus sequences at the 3' splice site. U2AF is required to stabilize the association of the U2 snRNP with the branch point.

label.value: undecaprenyl-phosphate glucose phosphotransferase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-glucose + ditrans,octacis-undecaprenyl phosphate -eq- UMP + alpha-D-glucopyranosyl-diphospho-ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol.

label.value: endocytic targeting sequence binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a endocytic signal sequence, a specific peptide sequence, of 4-6 amino acids with an essential tyrosine (Y), found on cytoplasmic tails of some cell surface membrane proteins, which directs internalization by clathrin-coated pits.

label.value: Cbf1-Met4-Met28 complex

definition.value: A heteromeric complex consisting of Cbf1 and basic leucine zipper (bZIP) containing transcriptional activators, Met4 and Met28, that forms over the sequence TCACGTG in the upstream activating sequence (UAS) of genes involved in sulfur amino acid metabolism, resulting in their transcriptional activation.

label.value: UDP-N-acetyl-D-mannosamine dehydrogenase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-mannosamine + 2 NAD+ + H2O -eq- UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-mannosaminuronate + 2 NADH + 2 H+.

label.value: tRNA m6t6A37 methyltransferase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + tRNA containing N6-threonylcarbamoyladenosine -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + tRNA containing N6-methylthreonylcarbamoyladenosine.

label.value: Pip2-Oaf1 complex

definition.value: A heterodimeric complex consisting of Zn(2)Cys(6) containing transcription factors Pip2 and Oaf1. It binds to the oleate response element (ORE), found in the promoters of fatty acid-inducible genes in Saccharomyces where, in the presence of oleate this bound complex activates the transcription of genes encoding peroxisomal proteins.

label.value: spanning component of membrane

definition.value: The component of a membrane consisting of gene products and protein complexes that have some part that spans both leaflets of the membrane.

label.value: RHG protein domain binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an RHG (reaper|hid|grimm) domain|motif (AKA iap binding motif).

label.value: caspase binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a caspase family protein.

label.value: phosphoenolpyruvate transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphoenolpyruvate from one side of a membrane to the other.

label.value: regulation of transcription involved in anterior neural plate formation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter contributing to the formation of the anterior neural plate.
